description: Introduces some useful puzzle solvers, a reparty command, spam hider for Skyblock, and a ton more with lots to come in the future!
Modern rendering engine and client-side optimization mod for Minecraft
Sodium addon providing support for the Fabric Rendering API, based on Indigo
No-compromises game logic/server optimization mod
Rewrites the light engine to fix lighting performance and lighting errors
Makes the initialization of DataFixerUpper "lazy", making the game start more quickly
Reduce FPS lag with block entities, as well as customize them with resource packs
Memory usage optimizations
Improve performance when Minecraft is in the background.
lazy-language-loader improves loading times when changing your language by only reloading the language instead of all the game resources!
Features that shouldn't be in Sodium.
Fixes Minecraft client lag from receiving chat messages (for 1.17 and 1.16)
No-compromises lighting engine optimization mod
A mod to optimize the Minecraft networking stack
An extension for Mod Menu which allows you to manage your mods ingame
Fixes some annoying bugs in the Minecraft client
Changes Fullscreen to use a borderless window.
When crashing, you can go back to the title screen and keep playing, without needing to restart, alongside other things to make crashes more pleasant.
Adds a 'few' quality of life changes to the recipe book.
A Minecraft mod which adds more tooltips.
Clean up your chat by removing duplicate messages!

A dynamic lights mod for Fabric.
